ew light on British film history. From the early days of the Film Society, via the advent of the X certificate to the new possibilities of video and DVD, this book reveals the complex and detailed history of the distribution, exhibition, marketing and reception of French cinema in Britain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aMotion pictureszFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictures, FrenchzGreat Britain. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aarchival research.  aart history.  aartistic.  aaudiences.  abritish film culture.  abritish film.  acinema.  acontinental films.  aculture.  adetailed history.  aengaging.  aeurope.  aeuropean film industry.  afilm distribution.  afilm exhibition.  afilm history.  afilm markets.  afilm society.  aforeign films.  afrench cinema.  afrench films.  ahistorical.  ahistory criticism.  ahollywood.  ahumor and drama.  apage turner.  aperforming arts.  apop culture.  aretrospective.  aromance.1 aWheatley, Catherine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745379240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857453792423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857453792/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK